cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on scheduling in multi-channel wireless networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses achieving optimal throughput and delay performance, which are important topics in information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a scheduling policy for wireless networks, which can be seen as a control problem in systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the downlink of a single cell in 4G cellular networks, which is related to multimedia transmission. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper aims to design scheduling policies that can achieve good performance in terms of both throughput and delay, which falls under the category of performance evaluation and optimization.
